
                                                               *cursor-font*

    " PACKAGE::COMMON-WINDOWS

    VARIABLE
    *cursor-font*  -  the default font used by make-mouse-cursordnl

    DESCRIPTION
    This global variable is bound to the font that will be used  by  default
    if  you  supply a :source-index argument to make-mouse-cursor.  In other
    words, it is bound  to  a  font  which  is  the  default  value  of  the
    :source-font keyword argument to make-mouse-cursor.

    EXAMPLES
    ;;  The following are equivalent:
    (make-mouse-cursor :source-index 54 :mask-index 55)
    (make-mouse-cursor :source-index 54 :mask-index 55
                       :source-font *cursor-font*)

    SEE ALSO
    make-mouse-cursor












































